    "spell": {
        "name": "Corrosive Muck",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "text": "You create two puddles of acidic slime that hinder the movement of anyone who walks through them. The area of each pool becomes greater difficult terrain. Each round that a creature starts its turn in one of the pools or enters a pool during a move action it's using, it takes 8d6 acid damage with a basic Reflex save. A creature that critically fails its saving throw also takes 1d6 persistent acid damage. As normal, if a Large or larger creature starts its turn in both pools, it takes the damage only once.",
        "subtype": "spell",
        "spell_type": "spell",
        "rank": 5,
